.\" Manpage for bitcoin(1).
.TH BITCOIN 1 "2026-05-15" "1.15.0" "User Commands"

.SH NAME
bitcoin \- educational Bitcoin frontend (BIPs implemented end-to-end)

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B bitcoin
.RI [ options ]
.I command
.RI [ args ...]

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B bitcoin
is an educational Bitcoin frontend. It is built around four
design principles:

.IP \(bu 2
.B educational
\(em every subcommand cites the BIP it implements, and the
referenced spec is shipped locally under
.IR share/doc/bitcoin/bips/ .
.IP \(bu 2
.B functional
\(em the tool is a real wallet: derive addresses, build and
sign transactions, broadcast through one of three backends.
.IP \(bu 2
.B decentralized
\(em the wallet repository is a git repository the user owns;
seed material lives outside of
.B bitcoin
in
.BR secret (1)
so wallets can be pushed and pulled between machines without
leaking key material.
.IP \(bu 2
.B simple
\(em the tool is bash + standard Unix utilities. There is no
shared cryptography library; each BIP plugin reaches for the
primitives it needs (openssl, dc, basenc) and is otherwise
self-contained.

.PP
A wallet is a per-name git repository at
.IR $XDG_DATA_HOME/bitcoin/wallets/<name>/
that holds the signing context (config, descriptors, the
addresses ledger). The seed phrase itself lives in
.BR secret (1)
\(em
.B bitcoin
calls
.B "secret get <wallet>/seed"
on demand whenever it needs to derive a key.

.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-d
Enable debug output (
.IR set\ \-vx ).
.TP
.B \-q
Quiet mode \(em suppress info-level messages.
.TP
.B \-p
Prompt for a BIP-39 passphrase before any seed operation.
.TP
.B \-t
Test-mode placeholder.

.SH COMMANDS

Every subcommand below has its own man page accessible as
.BI bitcoin- <name> (1)
\(em see SEE ALSO for the family list, or run
.BI "man bitcoin-" "<name>"
directly.

.SS Generic
.TP
.B help \fR[\fIcommand\fR]
Print top-level help, or per-command help when
.I command
is given.
.TP
.B version
Print the package version.
.TP
.B modules
List the BIP plugins under
.IR libexec/bitcoin/ .

.SS BIP plugins
.TP
.BR bitcoin-bip13 (1)
Base58 encoding primitives \(em BIP-13.
.TP
.BR bitcoin-bip32 (1)
Hierarchical deterministic key derivation \(em BIP-32.
.TP
.BR bitcoin-bip39 (1)
Mnemonic generation and validation \(em BIP-39.
.TP
.BR bitcoin-bip173 (1)
Bech32 string encoding \(em BIP-173.
.TP
.BR bitcoin-bip174 (1)
Partially-signed Bitcoin transactions \(em BIP-174.
.TP
.BR bitcoin-bip340 (1)
Schnorr signatures over secp256k1 \(em BIP-340.
.TP
.BR bitcoin-bip341 (1)
Taproot output-key tweak / P2TR address \(em BIP-341.
.TP
.BR bitcoin-bip350 (1)
Bech32m string encoding \(em BIP-350.
.TP
.BR bitcoin-bip380 (1)
Output script descriptors \(em BIP-380.
.TP
.BR bitcoin-wif (1)
Wallet Import Format encode / decode.
.TP
.BR bitcoin-descriptor (1)
Output script descriptors (partially deprecated;
.BR checksum / verify / derive
forward to
.BR bitcoin-bip380 (1)
since 1.23.0).

.SS Object verbs
.TP
.BR bitcoin-wallet (1)
Wallet lifecycle, derivation, signing, sending, push / pull.
.TP
.BR bitcoin-tx (1)
Transaction as a first-class verb (build / sign / decode /
finalize / extract / broadcast).
.TP
.BR bitcoin-utxo (1)
UTXO coin control: list / freeze / unfreeze.
.TP
.BR bitcoin-tax (1)
Tax-label vocabulary and (in 1.25.0) reporting.
.TP
.BR bitcoin-price (1)
BTC/EUR historical price oracle (local cache).
.TP
.BR bitcoin-address (1)
Validate addresses and detect their type (P2PKH / P2SH / P2WPKH / P2WSH / P2TR).
.TP
.BR bitcoin-backend (1)
Select and query the active chain-data backend.
.TP
.BR bitcoin-daemon (1)
Start / stop / monitor the local
.BR bitcoind .

.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B SELF_DEBUG
Enable shell tracing for any
.B bitcoin
process.
.TP
.B SELF_QUIET
Suppress info-level log lines.
.TP
.B SELF_LIBEXEC
Override the libexec directory used to find BIP plugins.
.TP
.B BITCOIN_BACKEND
Override the active backend for this shell (
.BR mempool ,
.BR bitcoind ,
.BR blockstream ).
Takes precedence over
.IR $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/bitcoin/backend .
.TP
.B BITCOIN_MEMPOOL_URL
Base URL for the mempool.space backend (default
.IR https://mempool.space ).
.TP
.B BIP39_PASSPHRASE
Optional BIP-39 passphrase consumed by
.BR "bitcoin bip39 mnemonic-to-seed" .
.TP
.B XDG_DATA_HOME
Wallet repositories live under
.IR $XDG_DATA_HOME/bitcoin/wallets/ .
.TP
.B XDG_CONFIG_HOME
Backend selection persists in
.IR $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/bitcoin/backend .
.TP
.B XDG_SHARE_HOME
The BIP-39 wordlist is read from
.IR $XDG_SHARE_HOME/bitcoin/bip39/<lang>.txt .

.SH FILES
.TP
.I $XDG_DATA_HOME/bitcoin/wallets/<name>/
Per-wallet git repository: config, descriptors, addresses
ledger.
.TP
.I $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/bitcoin/backend
Active backend (one line, one name).
.TP
.I share/doc/bitcoin/bips/bip-NNNN.mediawiki
Vendored BIP source documents (FEAT-017).
.TP
.I libexec/bitcoin/<plugin>
Per-BIP plugin script.

.SH EXIT STATUS
Zero on success; non-zero on failure. Every failure branch
emits at least one
.IR warn / error / fatal
line on stderr that names the condition and the offending
value (per
.IR skills/logging.md ).

.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
The cold-signing flow:
.PP
.RS
.EX
$ bitcoin wallet new alice
$ bitcoin wallet derive alice
bc1q...
$ # (fund the address from a faucet, wait for a confirmation)
$ bitcoin wallet balance alice
100000
$ bitcoin wallet send alice bc1qrecipientaddr... 50000
<txid>
.EE
.RE

.PP
The same flow split across two machines (hot-build, cold-sign):
.PP
.RS
.EX
hot$  bitcoin tx build alice bc1qrecipient 50000 > tx.psbt
cold$ bitcoin tx sign  alice < tx.psbt | bitcoin bip174 finalize > signed.psbt
hot$  bitcoin bip174 extract < signed.psbt | bitcoin tx broadcast alice
.EE
.RE

